This paper focuses on the motivation of workers involved in crowd employment, specifically micro-tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), as it deals with the interaction between humans and technology. The paper also touches upon issues related to cyberpsychology (cs.CY), social computing (cs.SI), software engineering (cs.SE), and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV). However, since the focus is on the motivation of workers, the first three categories are more likely to be relevant. Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of crowd employment, which could fall under the category of computational engineering (cs.CE) or systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper also mentions ethical issues related to crowd employment, which could fall under the category of security and privacy (cs.CR) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
